Sentencas: Micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cells (MT-SPFC) have emerged as a potential alternative for efficient energy generation.
Titulo: Co-extruded triple-layer micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell: The influence of cathode extrusion rate on the fuel cell properties and performance

Sentencas: This study investigates the impact of cathode extrusion rates (ranging from 3 to 6 mL min-1) on the triple layer anode/electrolyte/cathode MT-SOFC fabricated via a simplified phase inversion-based co-extrusion/ co-sintering technique.
Titulo: Co-extruded triple-layer micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell: The influence of cathode extrusion rate on the fuel cell properties and performance

Sentencas: Higher cathode extrusion rates (6 mL min-1) indirectly thin the electrolyte layer, improving ion hopping efficiency between the cathode and anode.
Titulo: Co-extruded triple-layer micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell: The influence of cathode extrusion rate on the fuel cell properties and performance

Sentencas: Moreover, increasing the extrusion rate enhances anode thickness, providing ample electrode reaction sites and thereby enhancing the gas diffusion process.
Titulo: Co-extruded triple-layer micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell: The influence of cathode extrusion rate on the fuel cell properties and performance

Sentencas: The C6 sample attains a peak power density of 1.46 W cm-2 with 1.08 V OCV at an optimum 800 degrees C operating temperature, which is high for MT-SOFCs in high-temperature applications.
Titulo: Co-extruded triple-layer micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell: The influence of cathode extrusion rate on the fuel cell properties and performance

Sentencas: There was a 71.8 % increase in power density for C6 when the temperature changed from 750 degrees C to 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Co-extruded triple-layer micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell: The influence of cathode extrusion rate on the fuel cell properties and performance

Sentencas: The composite cathode material fulfilled both the electronic and ionic conductivity requirements.
Titulo: Co-extruded triple-layer micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell: The influence of cathode extrusion rate on the fuel cell properties and performance

Sentencas: The optimal cathode extrusion rate for this simplified MT-SOFC fabrication was found to be 6 mL min-1.
